cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and document summarization. It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as summarization is a common task in this field. The use of neural networks suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the attention and distraction models used in the paper suggest it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
